  <h1>
    Scratch, a Standard Notes editor extension
  </h1>
  <p>
    Scratch is an editor extension for <a href="https://standardnotes.org/">Standard Notes</a>, a note-taking app that emphasizes privacy, security, and sustainability. If you don‚Äôt know what Standard Notes is, you are probably in the wrong place.
  </p>
  <p>
    Scratch includes most of the text editing features you would expect for taking notes, like lists, checkboxes, basic text formatting, smart copy/paste, and hotkeys. It uses the library <a href="https://prosemirror.net/">ProseMirror</a> to make those features possible. This page is an instance of the editor. Give it a try!
  </p>
  <h2>
    Installation
  </h2>
  <p>
    To use the Scratch editor in Standard Notes, click Extensions in the lower left hand corner of the desktop app. Click ‚ÄúImport Extension‚Äù and paste in the following url: <a href="http://sn-scratchpad-editor.firebaseapp.com/ext.json">http://sn-scratchpad-editor.firebaseapp.com/ext.json</a>. You will then have access to the editor on all the Standard Notes apps and will receive updates to the extension automatically.
  </p>
  <h2>
    Formatting your notes
  </h2>
  <p>
    Scratch includes a number of ways to format your notes. It has <strong>bold</strong>, <em>italic</em>, and <code>monospace</code> text, and it lets you add <a href=".">links</a>. It includes two levels of heads, two types of lists, and todo items that have a checkbox. Scratch tries to be smart about spacing so that you don‚Äôt have to insert empty lines.
  </p>
